[00:10.40]I don’t scare easy, but I don’t sleep deep
[00:16.44]Every sound’s got a shadow it keeps
[00:22.48]I reed the room like there's a loaded gun
[00:28.52]Smile on my face, but I’ve already run
[00:34.56]I trust in pieces, not all at once
[00:40.60]Every promise feels like it wants to jump
[00:46.64]I used to dream loud, used to feel safe
[00:52.68]Now every hope’s got a fracture line traced
[00:58.71]It didn’t break me, it bent my mind
[01:04.75]Taught my heart how to stay two steps behind
[01:10.79]I learned survival before I learned peace
[01:16.83]I hear alarms where there’s no real heat
[01:22.87]I’m not the same, always looking to the end
[01:28.91]Some wounds don’t bleed; they just rearrange who you’ve been
[01:34.95]I remember details nobody recalls
[01:40.99]The way silence screams, the rise before the fall
[01:47.03]I flinch at kindness, brace for the turn
[01:53.07]Even good love feels like something to earn
[01:59.11]I hold my breath in ordinary days
[02:05.15]Like calm is just a trick that fades
[02:11.19]I don’t forget, I just file it away
[02:17.23]Every moment weighed like it’s evidence
[02:23.27]It didn’t break me, it bent my mind
[02:29.31]Taught my thoughts how to run and hide
[02:35.35]I learned defense before I learn what to see
[02:41.39]Built walls out of what was left of the pieces of me
[02:47.43]I’m still standing, but I stand hyper aware
[02:53.47]Some damage doesn’t show, it sharpens your stare
[02:59.51]If I seem distant, I’m just avoiding the crowded room
[03:05.55]If I go quiet, I’m fighting old wounds
[03:11.59]I’m not cold, I’m conditioned
[03:17.63]Not weak, just listening
[03:23.67]It didn’t end me, it changed my view
[03:29.71]Turned the world into shades of untrue
[03:35.75]But I’m still here, still choosing to stay
[03:41.79]Still learning how to feel without bracing for pain
[03:47.83]I’m more than what I went through
[03:53.86]But it left fingerprints inside my view
[03:59.90]I’m healing slow, but I’m healing real
[04:05.94]Learning safety is something you feel
